@c -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node Introduction
@chapter Introduction

Guile-PNM is a @url{https://www.gnu.org/software/guile/, GNU Guile} library
for NetBPM (PNM) format.

@include guile-pnm-installation.texi

@c -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node API Reference
@chapter API Reference

This chapter describes the Guile-PNM API.

@menu
* PNM::                  High-level procedures to read and write images.
* PNM Image::            PNM image type.
* Graphics::             PNM graphics.

@end menu

@c -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node PNM
@section PNM

@code{(pnm)} module contains the basic PNM procedures to read/write PNM
images.

@deffn {Scheme Procedure} pnm->scm [port=(current-input-port) @
                                   [#:debug-mode?=#f]

Read and parse PNM image data from a @var{port}, return an
instance of a @code{<pnm-image>} sub-class, or throw a @code{pnm-error} on
errors.

@end deffn

@deffn {Scheme Procedure} scm->pnm image @
                                   [port=(current-output-port)]

Convert an @var{image} to a PNM format, print the output to a @var{port}.

Return value is undefined.

@end deffn

@deffn {Scheme Procedure} pnm-type [port=(current-output-port)] @
                                   [#:debug-mode?=#f]

Read data from a @var{port} and determine if the data is a PNM image.  Return
the type of the image as a symbol, or #f if the input data is not a PNM image.

@end deffn

@c -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
@node PNM Image
@section PNM Image

@c -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
@subsection Generic PNM image

@deftp {Class} <pnm-image> [#:commentary=#f] @
                           [#:width=#f] @
                           [#:height=#f] @
                           [#:data=#()]

This class represents a generic PNM image.

Constructor parameters:

@table @asis
@item #:width
Image width.
@item #:height
Image height.
@item #:data (data <vector>)
Image data as a vector.
@item #:commentary (comment <string>)
An optional image commentary.
@end table

@end deftp

@deffn {Scheme Procedure} pnm-image-commentary image
Get an @var{image} commentary.
@end deffn

@deffn {Scheme Procedure} pnm-image-commentary-set! image commentary
Set an @var{image} commentary.
@end deffn

@deffn {Scheme Procedure} pnm-image-width image
@deffnx {Scheme Procedure} pnm-image-width-set! image
@deffnx {Scheme Procedure} pnm-image-height image
@deffnx {Scheme Procedure} pnm-image-height-set! image
Get or set an @var{image} width and height.
@end deffn

@deffn {Scheme Procedure} pnm-image-data image
@deffnx {Scheme Procedure} pnm-image-data-set! image
Get or set the @var{image} data.
@end deffn

@deffn {Scheme Procedure} pnm-image->pnm image port

Print an @var{image} to a @var{port}.

@end deffn

@c -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
@subsection PBM

@deftp {Class} <pbm-ascii-image> [#:commentary=#f] @
                                 [#:width=#f] @
                                 [#:height=#f] @
                                 [#:data=#()]

This class represents a PBM ASCII image.

@end deftp

@deftp {Class} <pbm-binary-image> [#:commentary=#f] @
                                  [#:width=#f] @
                                  [#:height=#f] @
                                  [#:data=#()]

This class represents a PBM binary image.

@end deftp

@deffn {Method} pnm-image->pbm-binary-image (image <pbm-ascii-image>)
Convert an ASCII (plain) PBM @var{image} to a binary PBM image.  Return a new
@code{<pbm-binary-image>} instance.
@end deffn

@deffn {Method} pnm-image->pbm-ascii-image (image <pbm-binary-image>)
Convert an binary PBM @var{image} to an ASCII (plain) PBM image.  Return a new
@code{<pbm-ascii-image>} instance.
@end deffn

